                  </persName>
            . I am an oilman, and live in Bunhill-row. On the 27th of October I saw the prisoner near Mr. Earp's door; he rose from the steps, and walked away -I saw he had something, I walked by his side about three houses, and then asked what he had got; he said, "Nothing, but what is my own:" I said, "What is it?" he said,"A cloak;" I collared him - he said, "I picked it up, don't collar me, I'll give it you;" I took him to Mr. Earp's, who claimed it.</p>
